  keywords = {ME/CFS, myalgic encephalomyelitis, minocycline, neuroinflammation, microglia, treatment, open-label},
  note = {Open-label prospective study of oral minocycline (100 mg/day for 42 days) in 100 ME patients. Favorable response (performance status improvement ≥2 points) in 27 patients (27\%); best response in patients within 6 months of disease onset. Rationale: minocycline attenuates microglial activation and exerts anti-inflammatory, neuroprotective effects. 38\% discontinued due to adverse effects (nausea, dizziness). No control group. Low certainty due to design.}
