  keywords = {MCAS, diagnosis, management, practical approach, tryptase, antihistamine, epinephrine},
  certainty = {0.65},
  research_stream = {mcas-primary-driver},
  note = {ECNM--AIM endorsed practical Canadian guideline. Stepwise diagnostic framework: (1) confirm episodic, severe, multi-system presentation; (2) exclude secondary causes (food allergy, NSAID hypersensitivity); (3) obtain objective biomarkers (acute tryptase or urinary mediators); (4) evaluate for clonal mast cell disorders. Management: epinephrine autoinjector for acute episodes; prophylactic H1/H2 antihistamines for recurrence. Notes that access to key diagnostic tools remains limited. Aligns with ECNM--AIM international consensus.}
