  note = {25 healthy controls, 27 ME/CFS, 20 Long COVID donors. Flow cytometry, RNA-seq, mass spectrometry. Both conditions show elevated ROS and aberrant ROS clearance in memory lymphocytes: elevated glutathione, reduced mitochondrial SOD2, GPx4-mediated lipid oxidative damage. Sex-specific: females show elevated ROS; males show elevated lipid oxidative damage. Confirms oxidative stress as a shared ME/CFS/Long COVID signature. PNAS 2025.}
