  note = {Single-arm, open-label, before-and-after study (n=26, 19 completers) of oral magnesium 532mg/day for 3 months at Mayo Clinic, Scottsdale. For subjects with slight or greater impairment on THI/TSS, extent of handicap significantly decreased (p=0.03). Patients who ranked slight or greater on THI/TSS before intervention showed significant decrease in tinnitus severity at post-testing (p=0.008). Suggests magnesium may have beneficial effect on perception of tinnitus-related handicap}
}

