  note = {Detailed mechanistic review of quinolinic acid (QUIN) neurotoxicity. QUIN is an NMDA receptor agonist that at sub-threshold concentrations triggers excitotoxic cascades through: NMDA receptor overactivation, oxidative stress, mitochondrial dysfunction, cytoskeletal disruption, and apoptosis. Multiple non-NMDA targets explain why QUIN toxicity exceeds pure receptor pharmacology. Directly relevant to ME/CFS kynurenine excitotoxicity hypothesis.}
