  keywords = {ME/CFS, Long COVID, oxidative stress, ROS, MnSOD, glutathione peroxidase, lymphocytes, mitochondria, sex differences},
  note     = {Flow cytometry and omics study of peripheral blood lymphocytes in healthy controls, ME/CFS (n not specified in abstract), and Long COVID. Both ME/CFS and LC exhibit elevated oxidative stress, especially in memory lymphocyte subsets. Key findings: (1) elevated glutathione (GSH) levels, particularly in female subjects across B cells, CD4, and CD8 T cells; (2) decreased mitochondrial superoxide dismutase (MnSOD) protein levels; (3) GPX4-mediated lipid oxidative damage. Sex-specific patterns: females have higher total ROS and mitochondrial calcium; males show normal ROS but greater lipid oxidative damage. Excess lymphocyte ROS consumes host energy and contributes to fatigue. Metformin reduces T cell hyperproliferation associated with elevated ROS. Published July 2025 in PNAS.},
